# This repo is tracked via an allowlist: a global core.excludesFile may
# blanket-ignore every file (the "* + !*/" template), so the "!" rules below
# re-include exactly what the project ships. On a machine without such a global
# template these "!" lines are harmless no-ops. The denylist at the end always
# applies (it overrides the allowlist), so build output, secrets and IDE files
# stay out of the repo either way.

# --- Allowlist: source & project files ---
!*.go
!go.mod
!go.sum
!Dockerfile
!*.md
!*.json
!*.yml
!*.yaml
!*.example
!LICENSE
!.gitignore
!.dockerignore

# --- Denylist: never track (overrides the allowlist above) ---
# Compiled binary, test & coverage artifacts
/immich-exporter
*.test
*.out
coverage.txt
coverage.html
# GoReleaser local build output
/dist/
# Local secrets / config (may contain a token); committed templates are
# deploy/.env.example and deploy/config.example.yml
.env
deploy/.env
/config.yml
/config.yaml
# IDE / editor cruft
/.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
# OS cruft
.DS_Store
